  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "To filter out US election news from your Quora feed, you can try the following methods:\n\n1. **Unfollow Topics**: If you follow topics related to US elections or politics, you can unfollow them. Go to your profile, check the \"Topics\" section, and unfollow any topics that are related to US elections.\n\n2. **Adjust Your Feed Preferences**: Quora may allow you to customize your feed based on your interests. Check if you can adjust your preferences under the settings menu.\n\n3. **Hide Questions**: If you see a question related to US elections, you can click on the three dots (\u22ee) next to the question and select \"Hide\" or \"I don't want to see this\" to help tailor your feed over time.\n\n4. **Report Content**: If you repeatedly see content that you don\u2019t want (like US election news), consider reporting it. This action may help improve the recommendation algorithm.\n\n5. **Engage Differently**: Interact more with content that interests you (like specific hobbies or other topics). Quora uses your interactions to tailor your feed, so engaging with other topics may help shift the content you see.\n\n6. **Provide Feedback**: If applicable, provide feedback to Quora about the types of content you'd prefer to see less of.\n\nRemember that these changes might not filter out all related content immediately, but over time, your feed should start reflecting your preferences more closely.",
